search_query: US tariffs on cars imported from Vietnam 2025

What specific types of vehicles are included in the 'large-engine cars' category that Vietnam will provide zero tariffs for under the new US-Vietnam trade deal, and what are the technical specifications or engine sizes that define this category?

As of July 3, 2025, the US and Vietnam have agreed to a new trade deal where the US will impose a 20% tariff on imports from Vietnam [automotivelogistics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). This is lower than the 46% "reciprocal" duty that was previously threatened [automotivelogistics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [mufgresearch](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2). In return, Vietnam will eliminate tariffs on US products [epp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [time](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4) [automotivelogistics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [mufgresearch](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5) [freightwaves](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6) [cbsnews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [globalnews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8).

Here's a breakdown of the key aspects of the deal:

*   **Tariff Rates:**
    *   A 20% tariff will be applied to Vietnamese exports to the US [freightwaves](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6) [automotivelogistics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [epp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [globalnews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8) [mufgresearch](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [cbsnews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [vietnam-briefing](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).
    *   A 40% tariff will be imposed on goods transshipped through Vietnam, targeting products from third countries, especially China, that are labeled as Vietnamese to avoid higher tariffs [epp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [mufgresearch](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [automotivelogistics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5) [freightwaves](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6) [vietnam-briefing](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [globalnews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8).
    *   Vietnam will provide zero tariffs for US products, potentially including large-engine vehicles [epp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5) [time](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4) [mufgresearch](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [vietnam-briefing](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9) [cbsnews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [globalnews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8).

*   **Transshipment Concerns:** The 40% tariff on transshipments aims to prevent other countries from using Vietnam as a transit point to lower tariffs, particularly targeting China [epp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [automotivelogistics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [time](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). Enforcing this provision may be difficult and will require close monitoring of rules of origin [automotivelogistics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).

*   **Impact and Reactions:**
    *   China has reacted negatively to the US-Vietnam deal, with concerns that the transshipment tariffs are aimed at them [automotivelogistics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
    *   Experts believe the details of how "Transshipping" is defined and enforced will be crucial in determining the overall impact [mufgresearch](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2).
    *   The agreement is expected to strengthen the US economic ties with Vietnam [epp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).
    *   The US aims to reduce its trade deficit with Vietnam, which exceeded $123 billion in 2024 [epp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).

*   **Vietnam's Perspective:** Vietnam has committed to providing "preferential market access" for US goods, including large-engine cars [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1).

*   **Before the Deal:** Prior to this agreement, there was a 10% baseline import tax in place for almost all US trading partners, including Vietnam [automotivelogistics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [freightwaves](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6). In April 2025, the US announced a plan for 46% tariffs on Vietnamese goods [icis](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5) [frasersvn](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11).

It's important to note that some details of the agreement, such as the specific definition and enforcement of "transshipping," are still uncertain [mufgresearch](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1).
As of July 4, 2025, the new US-Vietnam trade deal includes a provision where Vietnam will provide zero tariffs for US products, including potential exports like "large-engine vehicles" [epp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0). These vehicles are often referred to as SUVs [stattimes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [epp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [theinvestor](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [ainvest](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).

While the exact technical specifications or engine sizes defining this "large-engine cars" category aren't explicitly detailed in the searched documents regarding the new US-Vietnam trade deal, several sources provide related context:

*   **General understanding:** The term "large-engine vehicles" is often used synonymously with SUVs [epp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [ainvest](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [theinvestor](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [stattimes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1). Examples of such vehicles include the Ford F-150 and GM Suburban [ainvest](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [ainvest](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4).
*   **Decree 73/2025/ND-CP:** While not directly tied to the US trade deal, this decree, effective March 31, 2025, amended import duty rates for certain goods, including automobiles [bakermckenzie](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [thesaigontimes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6). It mentions reduced tariffs for:
    *   Passenger vehicles with a shared luggage compartment and sports cars with 2,000-2,500cc engines [bakermckenzie](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
    *   Sedans with 2,000-2,500cc engines [bakermckenzie](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
    *   Four-wheel-drive vehicles [bakermckenzie](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
*   **HS Codes:** The Ministry of Finance in Vietnam has proposed adjustments to Most-Favored Nation (MFN) import tax rates on certain automobile models classified under HS codes [vietnamnews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7):
    *   8703.23.63: Passenger vehicles with a shared luggage compartment and SUVs with engine capacity over 2,000cc but not exceeding 2,500cc [vietnamnews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).
    *   8703.23.57: Sedan-type vehicles with the same engine capacity range (over 2,000cc but not exceeding 2,500cc) [vietnamnews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).
    *   8703.24.51: Four-wheel-drive vehicles [vietnamnews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).

It's important to note that while the US-Vietnam trade deal aims for zero tariffs on US-made "large-engine cars," Vietnam also imposes a 20% tariff on imports from the U.S [ainvest](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [automotivelogistics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8). Additionally, a 40% duty will be applied to goods transshipped from third countries [echemi](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9) [epp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [automotivelogistics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8) [aljazeera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10) [ainvest](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [cfr](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-11).
